# TSStart

An opnionated tanstack-start app template for create-tsstart.

## Acknowledgements

- [tss-app - tsstart is mostly based on this project with some personal changes](https://github.com/ally-ahmed/tss-app)

## What's included

- Runtime/Package Manager: bun
- Client: React + Vite
- Server: Vinxi
- RPC: tRPC
- DB: Drizzle + Libsql
- Auth: Lucia
- Route: Tanstack-Router
- Async: Tanstack-Query
- Table: Tanstack-Table + Shadcn
- State: Valtio
- Form: React-hook-form + zod
- UI: Shadcn + Tailwindcss
- Lint/Format: Eslint + Prettier
- Toast: Sonner
- Env: t3-oss/env-core

## Getting Started

Its easier to use the CLI to create the project.

### The CLI way

```bash
bun create tsstart <your-project-name>
```

### The manual way (repo clone)

Instead of cloning the repo with git clone, i recommend using degit to clone the repo.

```bash
bunx degit JohnC0de/tsstart <your-project-name>
```

Cd to the directory and install dependencies

```bash
cd <your-project-name>
bun install
```

Dont forget to setup the required env variables:

`GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=""`
`GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=""`

Setup the DB by creating the tables with drizzle-kit

```bash
bun push
```

Run app

```bash
bun dev
```
